Nigerian Medical Association Lagos State Chapter has reversed its stay-at home directive. Recall that the Nigerian Medical Association (NMA), Lagos State Chapter directed its members to immediately proceed on an indefinite sit-at-home protest, starting from 6.00p.m on Wednesday. The association gave the directive in a joint statement by its Chairman, Dr. Saliu Oseni, and Secretary, Dr Ramon Moronkola. However, the NMA National President Dr. Francis Faduyile, said: “I am not aware of a strike, but I am aware of a sit-at-home. A strike means there is an industrial dispute. However, a sit-at-home came to be because the Police has said that it will not exempt them from the restriction. Details Shortly…